# TypeScript Patterns

## Type Definitions
- Use interfaces from [src/types/index.ts](mdc:src/types/index.ts)
- Extend Prisma types when needed
- Use proper type annotations for all functions
- Avoid `any` type - use specific types or generics

## Component Props
```typescript
interface ComponentProps {
  // Use specific types, not any
  item: Item
  onUpdate: (item: Item) => void
  // Optional props with proper typing
  className?: string
}
```

## API Response Types
```typescript
// Use proper response typing
const response = await fetch('/api/items')
const items: Item[] = await response.json()
```

## Prisma Types
- Use Prisma generated types
- Extend with relations when needed
- Use proper type assertions for database operations

## Error Handling
```typescript
try {
  // Operation
} catch (error) {
  // Type the error properly
  const errorMessage = error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'Unknown error'
}
```

## Form Data Types
```typescript
interface FormData {
  name: string
  price: string // Keep as string for form inputs
  categoryId: string
  // Convert to proper types on submission
}
```